<subSubSection box="[199,1201,582,607]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1509]" box="[199,1201,582,607]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,583,607]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">Etymology.</emphasis>
The subspecies name refers to the body color pattern (body with two colors).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="79" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1509]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,618,643]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">Description.</emphasis>
Adult body length (without head and furca) 
<number box="[858,893,618,642]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="0.7">0.7</number>
–1.0 mm. With dark blue pigment on the dorsal and ventral sides of th.II to abd.II (including ventral tube), ant.I–IV (with increasing colour intensity towards the distal part of each segment), and cx.I–III; densely black pigmented ocular areas (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1136,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1786,1809]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,193,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[166,1452,193,1756]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Lepidocyrtus lanuginosus group: 1, Lepidocyrtus lanuginosus habitus; 2 Lepidocyrtus lanuginosus dorsal head; 3, Lepidocyrtus bicoloris sp. nov. habitus; 4, Lepidocyrtus cyaneus habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210425/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">
Fig. 
<number box="[1121,1136,690,714]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). The foremost part of the eye-patches connected by a pigmented band.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1509]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">
All morphological and chaetotaxic characters match those explained for 
<taxonomicName box="[1038,1206,763,787]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Lepidocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanuginosus">
<emphasis box="[1038,1206,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">L. lanuginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the following differences: Ratio antenna:cephalic diagonal 
<number box="[686,774,798,822]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="1.4" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.6</number>
. Labium chaetotaxy [M 
<number box="[1064,1072,814,828]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="1.0">1</number>
*] M 
<number box="[1135,1143,814,828]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="2.0">2</number>
R*EL 
<number box="[1209,1217,814,828]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="1.0">1</number>
L 
<number box="[1234,1242,814,828]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="2.0">2</number>
; one out of 
<number box="[1408,1436,798,822]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="22.0">22</number>
examined individuals with two M setae on one side of the labium. Interocular chaetotaxy with ciliated setae (s, t, p), and 
<number box="[235,277,873,897]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
scales. Abd.II seta ml present in three out of 
<number box="[782,810,873,897]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="22.0">22</number>
examined individuals (
