<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="79" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1509]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1197,1222]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">Discussion.</emphasis>
Color pattern is usually a useful discriminating character in 
<taxonomicName box="[1142,1311,1197,1221]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lepidocyrtinae">Lepidocyrtinae</taxonomicName>
(even in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,329,1233,1257]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Entomobryidae</taxonomicName>
). The &quot;color pattern species&quot; coined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoshii" box="[787,942,1233,1257]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" refString="Yoshii, R. (1989). On some Collembola of new Caledonia, with notes on the &quot; colour pattern species &quot;. Contributions from the Biological Laboratory of the Kyoto University, 27, 233 - 259." type="journal article" year="1989">
Yoshii (
<number box="[876,934,1233,1257]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for tropical Entomobryoidea argues that in the absence of diagnostic morphological characters, differences in color pattern were sufficient to define valid species. The molecular analysis of 
<bibRefCitation author="Soto-Adames" box="[543,778,1305,1329]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" refString="Soto-Adames, F. N. (2002) Molecular phylogeny of the Puerto Rican Lepidocyrtus and Pseudosinella (Hexapoda: Collembola), a validation of Yoshii's &quot; color pattern species &quot;. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 25, 27 - 42." type="journal article" year="2002">
Soto-Adames (
<number box="[711,770,1305,1329]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
on 
<taxonomicName box="[820,966,1305,1329]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Lepidocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[820,966,1305,1329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">Lepidocyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1021,1178,1305,1329]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Pseudosinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1021,1178,1305,1329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">Pseudosinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also demonstrated this point. The new species is very close to 
<taxonomicName box="[590,755,1342,1366]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Lepidocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanuginosus">
<emphasis box="[590,755,1342,1366]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">L. lanuginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[810,929,1343,1366]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Lepidocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneus">
<emphasis box="[810,929,1343,1366]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">L. cyaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Of this two species 
<taxonomicName box="[1164,1293,1342,1366]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Lepidocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicoloris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1164,1293,1342,1366]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">L. bicoloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1300,1390,1342,1366]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1300,1390,1342,1366]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be differentiated by the body color pattern: blue pigment on th.II to abd.II in 
<taxonomicName box="[1040,1171,1377,1401]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Lepidocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicoloris">
<emphasis box="[1040,1171,1377,1401]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">L. bicoloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without pigment in 
<taxonomicName class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Lepidocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanuginosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">L. lanuginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and dark blue pigmented in 
<taxonomicName box="[622,743,1415,1438]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Lepidocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneus">
<emphasis box="[622,743,1415,1438]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">L. cyaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, the new species has a size slightly smaller than the others, abd.IV seta Fe 
<number box="[438,451,1449,1473]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="4.0">4</number>
is a smooth mesochaeta, and shows variability in the presence or absence of abd.II seta ml, the number of unguis teeth, and the empodial denticulation (see 
<tableCitation box="[913,998,1485,1509]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="11.[151,235,1176,1197]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,1407,2029]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="TABLE 3. Lepidocyrtus lanuginosus group. Some characters of adult specimens. Long: body length in mm without head and furca; Body pigment: extension of body pigmentation; Cephalic A: number of setae in dorsal cephalic row A; Labium: chaetotaxy of posterior labial row; Abd. II seta ml: presence / absence of abd. II seta ml; Abd. IV seta Fe 4: morphology of abd. IV seta Fe 4, sm—smooth mesochaeta, cM—ciliated macrochaeta; Abd. IV seta E 4 p: morphology of abd. IV seta E 4 p, sm—smooth mesochaeta, cM—ciliated macrochaeta; TV lat flap: number of setae on lateral flap of the ventral tube, c—ciliated seta, s—smooth seta; Troch org: number of setae on trochanteral organ (third leg); Unguis teeth: number of inner odd teeth of the unguis; Unguiculus: morphology of the unguiculus outer margin. In brackets number of specimens." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/75D5662DFFB5FFBDFF11FB3DFB14520E" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" tableUuid="75D5662DFFB5FFBDFF11FB3DFB14520E">
Table 
<number box="[982,998,1485,1509]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" value="3.0">3</number>
</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
